revision.text:
[[Image:Tado Shrine.jpg|thumb|right|The entrance to Tado Shrine during the Tado Festival]] {{nihongo|'''Tado Shrine'''|多度大社|Tado Taisha}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in the [[Tado, Mie|Tado-chō]] area of the city of [[Kuwana, Mie|Kuwana]] in [[Mie Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is well known for its [[Tado Festival]], which takes place on [[May 4]] and [[May 5|5]] every year. The shrine has five nationally-designated Important Cultural Properties and one prefecturally-designated.
==Festivals== * '''[[Tado Festival]]''' ([[May 4]]&ndash;[[May 5|5]]): The largest of the events at the shrine, it involves young men riding horses up a hill and over a wall. * '''Chōchin Festival''' (Saturday and Sunday in late-July): A lantern festival. * '''Yabusame Festival''' ([[November 23]]): A horseback riding archery competition.
==External links== *[http://www.tadotaisya.or.jp/ Tado Shrine homepage] {{ja icon}}
{{coord|35|08|07.8|N|136|37|21.5|E|region:JP_scale:30000_source:jawiki|display=title}}
[[Category:Mie Prefecture]] [[Category:Shinto shrines in Mie Prefecture]]
[[ja:多度大社]]

